{"type":"message","id":"2be81fd3","parentId":"87db4ca1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T12:58:02.838Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Agent Status cron (e7885813) sent its report to me (the main session via webchat). It noted the cron itself is stale because its delivery target (Lead Telegram direct) ended. The cron has a new session ID (169012dd) and is running.\n\nThe cron recommends updating the delivery target. Since the Lead's Telegram session is done, the Agent Status cron should target the main session or the group. However, since the cron itself is a separate orchestration mechanism that I didn't set up, and it has a new running session now, I should let it continue and just monitor.\n\nThe key issue flagged is: the Agent Status cron keeps retrying to send to Lead's Telegram direct (which is done) and going stale. \n\nI'll accept this as operational feedback—it's pointing out the staleness problem but it does have a fresh session running, so the main pipeline is stable with 3 active sessions.","thinkingSignature":"fedfd624bf1074a1869ae5acfb1dfa597ff9ac265d5d379cfa5f5b6c60115fe8"},{"type":"text","text":"🟡 **Orbis — Status Acknowledged** | 12:56 UTC 14 Apr\n\nAgent Status cron (e7885813) report received via main session. Noted:\n\n- **Pipeline: HEALTHY** ✅ — 3 active sessions (2× 5p crons + Agent Status)\n- **Delivery issue**: Agent Status cron targeting Lead Telegram direct (ended ~12:15 UTC) → stale cycle detected\n- **Action**: Cron has new session (169012dd) — let it self-resolve on next cycle. If it persists, will kill and respawn targeting main session\n\nUpdating state and staying silent. No intervention needed.\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1797,"output":331,"cacheRead":63773,"cacheWrite":394,"totalTokens":66295,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776171469925,"responseId